  "prompt": "What is fossil fuel?",
  "response": "Fossil fuels are energy sources formed from the remains of ancient plants and animals that lived millions of years ago. Over time, these organic materials were buried under layers of sediment and subjected to heat and pressure, resulting in the formation of coal, oil, and natural gas. Fossil fuels are composed primarily of carbon and hydrogen, and they can be burned to release energy for various uses, such as electricity generation, heating, and powering vehicles. The combustion of fossil fuels, however, releases greenhouse gases like carbon dioxide, contributing to climate change and environmental pollution.",
